The paper deals with optimization problems and relaxations of pseudo-boolean functions, which are common topics in computer science. The use of bisubmodular functions and their relationship with totally half-integral relaxations suggests that the paper may belong to the categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of relaxations in machine learning and artificial intelligence, which could place it in the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves mathematical programming and optimization, which could place it in the category of Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
